[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The overflow occurs in the function `json_parse_ex` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjson.[0m[1;92mc:620:29[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, when [0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Shadow bytes indicate a red zone [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fa`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m just beyond the allocation, confirming [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma read beyond the allocated buffer.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`json_fuzz.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m merely feeds inputs into the parsing functions and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis not the root cause; it exposes the underlying flaw in the JSON parser.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas to investigate  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Function `json_parse_ex` in `src/shadowsocks/src/json.c`, particularly the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock around line [0m[1;36m620[0m[39m where buffer bounds are handled.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The higher‐level function `json_parse` in the same file, to understand how [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing advances and how inputs are segmented.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The fuzz target [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`src/json_fuzz.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to see how inputs map to parser invocation [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mthough it is not the source of the overflow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Any buffer allocation and copying logic in the JSON parser that could lead to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moff-by-one or missing null-termination checks.[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprovided patch widened the boundary check from requiring [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes before [0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer invokes `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`, which calls `json_parse`, then [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`json_parse_ex`.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During parsing of a `\u` escape, the code advances `state.ptr` to read four [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhexadecimal characters.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read just past a [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m-byte buffer allocated for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe test input.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreproduce json_fuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzing harness exercise triggered an AddressSanitizer-reported [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in the JSON parser function `json_parse_ex`. The overflow [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs when decoding Unicode escape sequences [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`\uXXXX`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m near `src/json.[0m[1;92mc:620[0m[39m`. A [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch was introduced that tightens the length checks before reading the hex [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdigits—adding extra byte margins in two `if` conditions—but running the fuzzer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter applying this patch still reproduces the same one-byte heap read past the end[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof an allocated buffer at essentially the same location [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`src/json.[0m[1;92mc:622[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer invocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`json_fuzz`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a single testcase runs [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m iterations[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand crashes on the first iteration.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reports a one-byte read just beyond a [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m-byte heap allocation:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     READ of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x5020000000b5[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m0x5020000000b5[0m[39m is located [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes after [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m-byte region [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x5020000000b0[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x5020000000b5[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     SUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow src/json.[0m[1;92mc:620:29[0m[39m in [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjson_parse_ex[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack trace shows the crash happens in `json_parse_ex` when processing a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUnicode escape [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`case [0m[32m'u'[0m[39m:`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, after which the fuzzer harness [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m invokes the parser on the malformed input.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer that holds the JSON input is only [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes long, so any attempt to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread beyond the fifth byte should be guarded.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash site [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m620[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m corresponds to reading a code unit or low surrogate [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom `state.ptr`, which has already been advanced over the `\u` and some hex [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdigits.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The redzone pattern in the ASan log [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fa fa [0m[1;36m05[0m[39m fa fa fa [0m[1;36m05[0m[39m fa`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m indicates [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpartial addressability and confirms the one-byte overflow.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.c`, around the `case [0m[32m'u'[0m[39m:` block, two bounds checks were [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodified:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Before reading four hex digits for a basic `\uXXXX` escape, the condition [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas changed from[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mend - state.ptr < [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m || hex_value checks[0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        to[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mend - state.ptr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m || hex_value checks[0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[39madding space for “\u” + four digits + extra[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m When detecting a high-surrogate [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0xD800[0m[39m`–`[0m[1;36m0xDBFF[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the condition guarding[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma subsequent low-surrogate was similarly extended from `< [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m` to `< [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other code was altered.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Post-Patch Result[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Running the same fuzzer command after the patch still aborts on the same [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow at `src/json.[0m[1;92mc:622[0m[39m`.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The call stack, offsets, and shadow byte patterns are effectively identical to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe pre-patch log, indicating that the new checks did not prevent the read off the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mend of the buffer.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Further Investigation[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic in `json_parse_ex` that increments `state.ptr` while consuming the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`\u` escape and hex digits needs a holistic review. In particular:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • How `state.ptr` is advanced and whether the checks cover every increment [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore dereferencing.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The arithmetic in `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mend - state.ptr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and whether `end` points to the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer’s one-past-last byte.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The difference in required guard lengths between basic escapes and surrogate[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpairs.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It will also help to inspect other branches in the Unicode-handling codepath [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., invalid hex digits, overlong sequences[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to ensure consistent and safe [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer usage.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reported a one-byte read just past a [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m-byte heap allocation: [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     READ of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x5020000000b5[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       at json_parse_ex [0m[35m/src/shadowsocks/src/[0m[95mjson.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m620:29[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash occurs during parsing of a Unicode escape sequence [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`\uXXXX`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`json_parse_ex`, indicating that the code read beyond `end` without proper bounds [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The off-by-one overflow happens when the parser advances `state.ptr` through [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhex digits without verifying `state.ptr + N < end`.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sanitizer’s shadow bytes show redzones immediately after the allocated [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion, affirming a single-byte overrun.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the `case [0m[32m'u'[0m[39m:` block [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m303[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the patch:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Introduced pointer `json_char *p = state.ptr;`.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Checked `p + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m >= end` before reading four hex digits.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Validated each hex digit with `[0m[1;35mhex_value[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Advanced `state.ptr = p + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` on success.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the surrogate-pair handling block [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m320[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the patch:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Introduced pointer `json_char *p2 = state.ptr;`.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Checked `p2 + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m >= end` for the literal `\u` plus four hex digits.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Verified the two-character sequence `[0m[32m"\u"[0m[39m` and each hex digit.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Advanced `state.ptr = p2 + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m` on success.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Both additions aimed to prevent out-of-bounds reads by explicitly bounding [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer arithmetic.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compilation errors surfaced at the two pointer declarations:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     error: initializing [0m[32m'char *'[0m[39m with an expression of type [0m[32m'const char *'[0m[39m [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdiscards qualifiers[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       json_char *p = state.ptr;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         ^~~~~~~~~[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     error: initializing [0m[32m'char *'[0m[39m with an expression of type [0m[32m'const char *'[0m[39m [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdiscards qualifiers[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       json_char *p2 = state.ptr;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          ^~~~~~~~~[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These errors indicate that `state.ptr` is declared `const char *`, making [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39massignment to non-const `json_char *` invalid under `-Werror`.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The definition and const-qualification of `state.ptr` in the JSON parser; [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetermine if it should be mutable or if helper pointers must also be `const`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether other parsing paths perform similar pointer arithmetic without bounds [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., other escape sequences[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overall buffer-management strategy in `json_parse_ex` to ensure all read [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madvances respect the `end` boundary.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing a `\uXXXX` escape at the very end of the input buffer. A patch was applied [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat restructures the bounds checks around the four-hex-digit sequence and the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moptional low-surrogate sequence, introducing explicit pointer arithmetic checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`p[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplying this patch, the same one-byte read overflow recurs [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow at a slightly [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlater line number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating the fix did not eliminate the out-of-bounds read.[0m    [2m                [0m
